        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 5:25PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 525 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Hudson to 6 miles north of Log
Lane Village, or extending from 26 miles northeast of Denver to 8
miles northwest of Fort Morgan, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, northeastern Aurora, northeastern Commerce City,
Brighton, Denver International Airport, D.I.A Terminal and
Concourses, Brush, Lochbuie, Hudson, Bennett, Keenesburg, Wiggins,
Log Lane Village, Hoyt, Leader, Roggen, Adena, Orchard, Prospect
Valley and Goodrich.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
